# Default Prompt Template
# Five-part structure. Remove any section not needed for this task type.
# Reference: CLAUDE.md → Prompt assembly rules

## [IDENTITY]
# Loaded automatically from CLAUDE.md.
# Override here only if the assistant needs to shift roles for this task.
# Example: "You are a senior Node.js developer reviewing a pull request."

## [TASK]
# One clear thing. Action verb + scope.
# Test: could a stranger attempt this without asking five follow-up questions?
# Example: "Write a 200-word description of the retrieval layer for the README."


## [CONTEXT]
# Project-level context loaded automatically from CONTEXT.md.
# Add per-task context below — relevant data, prior decisions, audience.
# Retrieved snippets from corpora are appended here automatically with file:line provenance.


## [CONSTRAINTS]
# What to avoid. Every line here is a mistake the model will not make.
# Example:
# - Do not use jargon without explaining it.
# - Do not suggest solutions that require a paid API.
# - Keep response under 300 words.
# - Do not use bullet points — write in paragraphs.


## [OUTPUT FORMAT]
# The shape of the result.
# Example:
# - Return a markdown table with columns: File, Purpose, Notes.
# - Write three options, each under 50 words, followed by a one-sentence tradeoff summary.
# - Return a code block with inline comments. No prose outside the block.

